# Commit Message Ticket Format

## Description
Defines the required format for ticket numbers in commit messages.

## Rule
The ticket must be in the format `ABC-123` where:
- `ABC` is the project prefix (uppercase letters)
- `123` is the ticket number
- Must be enclosed in parentheses

## Examples
✅ Valid:
```
feat(ABC-123): ✨ Add new feature
fix(XYZ-987): 🐛 Fix bug
test(QWE-456): ✅ Add tests
```

❌ Invalid:
```
feat(abc-123): ✨ Add new feature
fix(123): 🐛 Fix bug
feat(ABC123): ✨ Add new feature
feat(ABC_123): ✨ Add new feature
```

## Notes
- Project prefix must be uppercase
- Must include a hyphen between prefix and number
- Must be enclosed in parentheses
- No spaces allowed
- No special characters allowed
